  "2026-07-10T10:47:37.642Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence 2026-07-10: validate_resolution_missing_fields drifted 269 -> 272 (+3) in one day — the 2026-07-09 closes of pm-2ldo, pm-q6gx, pm-cu1i (all closed via close -m with strong prose close_reason but no structured resolution/expected/actual). Confirms the faucet is every routine agent close, not a legacy backlog: without a close-time signal the structured fields will keep losing to close_reason. Rate data point for prioritization: ~3/day at current agent throughput."
  "2026-07-10T16:20:54.345Z",maintainer-agent,"Faucet evidence 2026-07-10 (post PR #499): validate_resolution_missing_fields 272 -> 277. The +5 are the schema-fidelity bundle closures (pm-kfq5, pm-l6rz, pm-zazb, pm-b84u, pm-ghf1) — all closed with a substantive close_reason but no structured resolution/expected/actual triple, exactly the leak this item gates. Third consecutive pass with growth (269 -> 272 -> 277); each shipped lane adds ~5. Other buckets steady: missing_linked_paths 154, orphaned_paths 124, missing_close_reason 18 (pm-e9zh), duplicate_issue_codes 1 (pm-pivf)."
  "2026-07-10T21:27:42.513Z",maintainer-agent,"Faucet evidence 2026-07-10 (post-PR#502): resolution_missing_fields 277 -> 278 (+1). The lane closed 8 items (pm-114v/l0bu/yl6c/hfg5/ol5v/6y58/z32q/w7jq) but only +1 leaked — close reasons were set on all 8; the +1 is a partial-fields close. Rate is falling versus the ~+5/lane baseline, but the faucet is still open until the close-time completeness gate ships."
  "2026-07-11T02:51:16.306Z",maintainer-agent,"Faucet evidence 2026-07-11: resolution_missing_fields HELD at 278 across PR#506's nine closes (pm-4ak1/5566/2vb2/768v/m0uc/mswi/qely/uwu0/uxmf) — first fully zero-leak lane observed (trend: +5/lane pre-#47, +1/8 on PR#502, 0/9 now). Close-time completeness discipline is landing without the gate; remaining 278 is legacy stock, so this item's value is now mostly ratchet-protection (prevent regression) + backfill, not stemming an active faucet."
  "2026-07-11T09:56:18.352Z",maintainer-agent,"Faucet trend update 2026-07-11 (post-PR#511): resolution_missing_fields HELD at 278 across 4 more lane closes (pm-s9iu/pm-0mjz/pm-o71e/pm-9qcr, all with structured resolutions) — SECOND consecutive zero-leak lane after PR#506's 9 closes. Two independent lanes now demonstrate close-time completeness is achievable by default; ratchet gate (fail on any increase above 278) is de-risked, remaining value is the legacy backfill half."
body: "## Problem\n`validate_resolution_missing_fields` keeps creeping (269 → 272 across 2026-07-09→10) even though `close_reason` is enforced: agents close items with a reason but skip the structured triple `resolution` / `expected_result` / `actual_result` (set via `pm close --resolution/--expected/--actual` or `pm update`). pm-e9zh backfills the pre-enforcement legacy set, but nothing stops NEW closes from adding to the worklist, so the backfill target moves.\n\n## Proposal\n1. Emit a completeness line in the `pm close` envelope when any of the three structured fields is absent (always on, one short line — token-cheap, mirrors the existing next_transition hint pattern).\n2. Add a governance settings key (e.g. `close.require_resolution_fields: off | warn | require`, default `warn`) so strict workspaces can hard-gate like `require_close_reason` already does.\n3. Contract + docs + completion wiring per the new-flag checklist; validate check text should point at the setting.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- Closing without the triple prints exactly one advisory line naming the missing fields and the flags to set them; with `require`, close exits non-zero with the same recovery bundle shape as close_reason_required.\n- `validate_resolution_missing_fields` stops growing on workspaces with warn/require enabled (verified in e2e fixture).\n- No output change when all three fields are provided.\n\n## Relation\nrelated pm-e9zh (legacy backfill) — this item is the faucet, e9zh is the mop."
